00:41:33.042 --> 00:41:35.009
Too many tax dollars
to try and hide.

766
00:41:35.147 --> 00:41:37.529
and-and off-world artifacts
are too profitable

767
00:41:37.667 --> 00:41:39.369
to leave in the hands
of appointed officials.

768
00:41:39.393 --> 00:41:42.120
especially after
the Nixon thing.

769
00:41:42.258 --> 00:41:45.882
Presidents are civilians again
after eight years. so...

770
00:41:46.020 --> 00:41:49.196
so there's no longer a reason
to read them in on any of this.

771
00:41:51.336 --> 00:41:54.512
I was a part of all that
until I saw what you just saw.

772
00:41:55.720 --> 00:41:59.102
This all stops now.

773
00:41:59.240 --> 00:42:00.828
What are you gonna do?

774
00:42:01.864 --> 00:42:06.420
Full disclosure
to the whole world all at once.

775
00:42:09.285 --> 00:42:12.115
Have you considered
what effect that'll have?

776
00:42:13.358 --> 00:42:15.015
On everything?

777
00:42:16.050 --> 00:42:17.431
What...

778
00:42:17.569 --> 00:42:19.260
It's not up to me
to decide if it's...

779
00:42:19.398 --> 00:42:22.229
if it's good or bad
for people to know.

780
00:42:22.367 --> 00:42:25.059
Then how is it up to you
to decide that the right to know

781
00:42:25.197 --> 00:42:27.475
outweighs the consequences
of knowing?

782
00:42:27.614 --> 00:42:29.374
Are you saying
we leave this up to WARDEX?

783
00:42:29.512 --> 00:42:31.894
'Cause they-they've already
decided this belongs to them.

784
00:42:32.032 --> 00:42:34.621
this core truth
about the universe.

785
00:42:34.759 --> 00:42:36.864
-It's wrong.
-You can't do that.

786
00:42:38.072 --> 00:42:39.695
Think about...

787
00:42:41.386 --> 00:42:42.801
People will see them as deities.

788
00:42:42.939 --> 00:42:44.838
They'll stop believing in God.

789
00:42:44.976 --> 00:42:46.736
Well. you left the church.

790
00:42:46.874 --> 00:42:48.289
Not because I stopped believing.

791
00:42:48.427 --> 00:42:50.026
because I could no longer say
with certainty

792
00:42:50.050 --> 00:42:51.430
that God is divine.

793
00:42:51.569 --> 00:42:54.572
but I believe profoundly
that he's essential.

794
00:42:56.401 --> 00:42:57.885
He's how we define ourselves.

795
00:42:58.023 --> 00:43:00.854
He's what keeps
whole civilizations together.

796
00:43:02.476 --> 00:43:05.237
We've been raised to believe
in a supreme being.

797
00:43:05.375 --> 00:43:09.034
and now you want to show us
actual supreme beings?

798
00:43:09.172 --> 00:43:10.829
People can't handle both.

799
00:43:13.418 --> 00:43:15.075
Of course they can.

800
00:43:15.213 --> 00:43:16.732
No. they can't.

801
00:43:17.767 --> 00:43:19.700
Look at our history
with any sudden change.

802
00:43:20.770 --> 00:43:24.981
And now. with the world about
to blow up in all our faces?

803
00:43:26.638 --> 00:43:31.056
You'll get panic and-and chaos.
and God help us.

804
00:43:35.336 --> 00:43:37.442
Hugo's expecting me to check in.

805
00:43:49.247 --> 00:43:50.869
No signal.

806
00:43:52.699 --> 00:43:54.493
No signal.

807
00:43:54.632 --> 00:43:56.668
I'll try the other side
of the hill.

808
00:44:26.767 --> 00:44:28.010
Okay.

809
00:44:28.148 --> 00:44:29.356
Unlock the door!

810
00:44:29.494 --> 00:44:30.668
-What?
-Jackson. come on!

811
00:44:30.806 --> 00:44:32.462
Oh. shit. Sorry.

812
00:44:33.636 --> 00:44:35.327
Oh. sorry. sorry.

813
00:44:35.465 --> 00:44:37.847
-Okay.
-Oh. my God.

814
00:44:43.750 --> 00:44:45.348
If you answer that in French.
I swear to God

815
00:44:45.372 --> 00:44:46.729
I'm marching you
right back inside.

816
00:44:46.753 --> 00:44:48.306
Hello?

817
00:44:48.444 --> 00:44:50.273
I've been
waiting a very long time

818
00:44:50.411 --> 00:44:52.551
to meet you. Ms. Fairchild.

819
00:44:52.690 --> 00:44:54.105
Who is this?

820
00:44:54.243 --> 00:44:55.865
A friend.

821
00:44:57.142 --> 00:44:59.835
And if I'm right about you.
Margaret.

822
00:44:59.973 --> 00:45:01.388
you'd know if I wasn't.

823
00:45:01.526 --> 00:45:02.907
No. I don't... I don't know you

824
00:45:03.045 --> 00:45:04.771
any more than I know
what's happening to me.

825
00:45:04.909 --> 00:45:07.083
Very few people could
manage this as well as you.

826
00:45:07.221 --> 00:45:09.027
-I'm not managing it. I'm not.
-Who-who is that?

827
00:45:09.051 --> 00:45:11.363
I am frightened.
I'm frightened out of my wits.

828
00:45:11.501 --> 00:45:15.471
Because you're just a passenger
on your way somewhere.

829
00:45:15.609 --> 00:45:17.289
-Let us help you get there.
-Help me how?

830
00:45:17.404 --> 00:45:18.474
What do you mean?

831
00:45:18.612 --> 00:45:19.924
-Is that the FBI?
-Shh!

832
00:45:20.062 --> 00:45:21.211
We want to offer you
our protection.

833
00:45:21.235 --> 00:45:22.616
We held back on reaching out

834
00:45:22.754 --> 00:45:24.652
until after we saw
your weather report.

835
00:45:24.791 --> 00:45:26.137
You held back?

836
00:45:26.275 --> 00:45:27.390
What do you mean?
What does that mean?

837
00:45:27.414 --> 00:45:29.174
Are you gonna need a lawyer?

838
00:45:32.937 --> 00:45:35.767
Who is 873-2626?

839
00:45:37.527 --> 00:45:38.874
Since you know that number.

840
00:45:39.012 --> 00:45:41.255
you must already know
who it belongs to.

841
00:45:43.602 --> 00:45:44.811
Kellner?

842
00:45:45.881 --> 00:45:46.881
Kellner?

843
00:45:46.916 --> 00:45:48.642
All right.

844
00:45:48.780 --> 00:45:50.299
Listen carefully.

845
00:45:50.437 --> 00:45:51.749
You cannot go home.

846
00:45:51.887 --> 00:45:53.278
If you have another direction
in mind.

847
00:45:53.302 --> 00:45:55.373
even a vague inclination.
follow it.

848
00:45:55.511 --> 00:45:57.202
If we can find you by phone.
others can

849
00:45:57.340 --> 00:45:59.100
-find you in the world.
-No. it's too late.

850
00:45:59.204 --> 00:46:00.585
They...
Uh. they already found me.

851
00:46:00.723 --> 00:46:03.312
Hang up immediately.
Destroy your phone.

852
00:46:03.450 --> 00:46:04.762
How will you find me?

853
00:46:04.900 --> 00:46:06.256
I have every confidence
you'll find us.

854
00:46:06.280 --> 00:46:07.281
Do it now.

855
00:46:09.111 --> 00:46:11.872
Wait. wait. What are you...
Wh-What are you doing?!

856
00:46:13.529 --> 00:46:14.529
Back up over the phone.

857
00:46:14.599 --> 00:46:16.359
-What?
-Back up!

858
00:46:16.497 --> 00:46:18.165
-Come on.
-Okay. I'd like to point out that I'm being

859
00:46:18.189 --> 00:46:20.329
extremely cool here
and that I'm rolling with it.

860
00:46:20.467 --> 00:46:22.469
and that was a $600 phone.

861
00:46:23.504 --> 00:46:25.504
Well. it's still a $600 phone
'cause you missed it.

862
00:46:25.541 --> 00:46:27.001
Jackson. pull forward
till you hear the crunch.

863
00:46:27.025 --> 00:46:28.026
-Come on.
-Sorry.

864
00:46:32.617 --> 00:46:34.688
Oh. my God. you missed it again.
Oh. my God.

865
00:46:34.826 --> 00:46:36.828
Okay. - What?

866
00:46:40.625 --> 00:46:41.937
Okay.

867
00:46:43.628 --> 00:46:46.010
Pull forward. Go. go. go.

868
00:46:47.632 --> 00:46:49.392
Keep going. Keep going.

869
00:46:58.677 --> 00:47:00.990
Okay. Okay.

870
00:47:01.128 --> 00:47:04.338
-Okay. let's go. Let's go.
-Uh... wh-where?

871
00:47:04.476 --> 00:47:06.030
-North.
-Why?

872
00:47:06.168 --> 00:47:07.490
Because that's where
Daniel Kellner is.

873
00:47:07.514 --> 00:47:09.033
Oh. my God.

874
00:47:09.171 --> 00:47:10.873
Who is this dude?
Is he some guy from your past

875
00:47:10.897 --> 00:47:12.426
-that you never told me about?
-I don't know. Jackson.

876
00:47:12.450 --> 00:47:13.772
-Or what is it?
-You're giving me a headache.

877
00:47:13.796 --> 00:47:14.521
I don't know
what I'm doing here.

878
00:47:14.659 --> 00:47:15.902
I don't know who he is.

879
00:47:16.040 --> 00:47:17.524
I just know
he's someplace north.

880
00:47:17.662 --> 00:47:18.662
That's all I know. okay?

881
00:47:18.697 --> 00:47:20.009
Oh. my God. What is that sound?

882
00:47:22.494 --> 00:47:24.496
-Your hailstorm.
-Wow.

883
00:47:24.634 --> 00:47:25.946
Weather Shimmy?

884
00:47:26.084 --> 00:47:28.328
Just drive. Just drive.

885
00:48:16.859 --> 00:48:19.379
You got Kellner on 2626.

886
00:48:21.105 --> 00:48:22.692
Look at the video
I just sent you.

887
00:48:22.830 --> 00:48:24.142
Okay. hold on.

888
00:48:30.631 --> 00:48:32.081
Yeah. So?

889
00:48:32.219 --> 00:48:34.014
She's the one
we've been waiting for.

890
00:48:34.152 --> 00:48:36.499
Her? Why?

891
00:48:36.637 --> 00:48:38.881
Did you not hear her?

892
00:48:39.019 --> 00:48:40.400
Yeah. I heard her.

893
00:48:40.538 --> 00:48:41.815
And you still ask why?

894
00:48:41.953 --> 00:48:43.713
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

895
00:48:43.851 --> 00:48:45.612
That's all she had to say?

896
00:48:47.062 --> 00:48:49.064
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know"?

897
00:48:49.202 --> 00:48:50.479
That's what she said?

898
00:48:50.617 --> 00:48:52.101
You didn't hear it?

899
00:48:53.585 --> 00:48:55.104
We all heard it.

900
00:48:55.242 --> 00:48:57.348
We couldn't understand it.
It's not English.

901
00:48:57.486 --> 00:48:59.005
Of course it is.

902
00:48:59.143 --> 00:49:01.076
I'm listening to it right now.

903
00:49:01.214 --> 00:49:03.123
I'm sending you to Kansas City.
where she's from.

904
00:49:03.147 --> 00:49:05.125
-We'll get a car to you.
-Leave tonight. - Hey. wait.

905
00:49:05.149 --> 00:49:06.781
-Wait a second. Wait a second.
-Do not travel by day.

906
00:49:06.805 --> 00:49:08.197
You're not hearing it?
It's-it's perfectly clear.

907
00:49:08.221 --> 00:49:09.301
Detour past tollbooths
and turnpikes.

908
00:49:09.325 --> 00:49:10.533
Hey. listen to me.

909
00:49:10.671 --> 00:49:11.855
Have you played this
to other people?

910
00:49:11.879 --> 00:49:13.847
Stay with me.

911
00:49:13.985 --> 00:49:16.608
A motel room key will be
in the car with directions.

912
00:49:16.746 --> 00:49:18.541
Santiago will retrieve you
in the morning.

913
00:49:18.679 --> 00:49:21.061
By then. I'll know
what comes next.

914
00:49:21.199 --> 00:49:23.788
Hugo. you're scaring
the shit out of me.

915
00:49:23.926 --> 00:49:27.550
There are two of you. Daniel.

916
00:49:27.688 --> 00:49:30.795
There's always been
just the two of you.

917
00:52:26.143 --> 00:52:27.661
Hello. Jane.

918
00:52:27.799 --> 00:52:29.560
Please.

919
00:52:30.940 --> 00:52:32.977
Have a seat.

920
00:52:38.638 --> 00:52:41.192
Where are you right now. Jane?

921
00:52:41.330 --> 00:52:43.021
What is your location?

922
00:52:44.299 --> 00:52:46.611
-I don't know.
-Relax. please.

923
00:52:50.028 --> 00:52:52.514
-Who are you?
-I'll ask the questions.

924
00:52:53.618 --> 00:52:55.344
Are you still with
Daniel Kellner?

925
00:53:01.557 --> 00:53:02.869
He's outside.

926
00:53:06.528 --> 00:53:08.115
Where were you last night?

927
00:53:17.711 --> 00:53:20.369
-BP's high but holding: 156/94.
-O2's decent at 96.

928
00:53:20.507 --> 00:53:22.451
-but sodium's climbing.
-Heart rate's hot. too... 118.

929
00:53:22.475 --> 00:53:23.659
-Potassium's borderline. too.
-Jane!

930
00:53:23.683 --> 00:53:25.202
-Stand by. Ringer's.
-Jane!

931
00:53:26.168 --> 00:53:27.687
Jane!

932
00:53:27.825 --> 00:53:30.068
Where were you last night?

933
00:53:31.277 --> 00:53:34.211
Monastery of St. Clare
of the Dawn.

934
00:53:34.349 --> 00:53:36.454
Monastery St. Clare?

935
00:53:36.592 --> 00:53:38.007
Of course.

936
00:53:38.145 --> 00:53:41.114
I remember St. Clare
from my Sunday school.

937
00:53:41.252 --> 00:53:43.150
She was too sick to go
to midnight Mass.

938
00:53:43.289 --> 00:53:45.877
and she had a vision
of it instead.

939
00:53:46.015 --> 00:53:48.501
She was in two places at once.
like me.

940
00:53:51.228 --> 00:53:53.264
Monastery of St. Clare. Got it.

941
00:53:53.402 --> 00:53:55.301
13 miles southeast
of the District.

942
00:53:55.439 --> 00:53:57.889
When you left.
which way did you drive?

943
00:54:01.617 --> 00:54:02.825
I don't know.

944
00:54:02.963 --> 00:54:04.482
Was the sun up?

945
00:54:07.623 --> 00:54:09.004
Yes.

946
00:54:09.142 --> 00:54:11.282
Did you drive into it
or away from it?

947
00:54:14.768 --> 00:54:16.391
It was on the right.

948
00:54:18.565 --> 00:54:19.980
I don't like you.

949
00:54:20.118 --> 00:54:21.879
Not required.

950
00:54:22.017 --> 00:54:23.467
Sun on the right.

951
00:54:23.605 --> 00:54:25.341
Sun on the right...
they're headed due north.

952
00:54:25.365 --> 00:54:26.642
possibly northwest.

953
00:54:26.780 --> 00:54:28.403
Could be on 27. 18
or the interstate.

954
00:54:28.541 --> 00:54:29.956
Interstate not likely.

955
00:54:30.094 --> 00:54:31.727
Focus on frontage roads
or county highways.

956
00:54:31.751 --> 00:54:34.271
Did you pass a street sign?

957
00:54:34.409 --> 00:54:35.824
Yes.

958
00:54:35.962 --> 00:54:37.688
What did it say?

959
00:54:42.037 --> 00:54:45.178
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

960
00:54:45.316 --> 00:54:47.698
Street sign.
"Silver Spring: 120 miles."

961
00:54:47.836 --> 00:54:50.459
I've got half
a dozen towns off the 26.

962
00:54:50.597 --> 00:54:53.773
Silver Hollow. Oakshade.
Ironmere. Stonemont...

963
00:54:53.911 --> 00:54:55.706
Try for more details. Jane.

964
00:54:55.844 --> 00:54:57.363
What else did you pass?

965
00:54:59.261 --> 00:55:00.331
A river.

966
00:55:00.469 --> 00:55:02.057
Passed a river.

967
00:55:02.195 --> 00:55:04.231
Did you see a sign for a town
after that?

968
00:55:06.475 --> 00:55:08.546
-Yes.
-What did it say?

969
00:55:13.102 --> 00:55:14.690
S-Sykesville.

970
00:55:14.828 --> 00:55:17.486
-Sykesville.
-Sykesville.

971
00:55:18.729 --> 00:55:21.179
Field is narrowed.
Track and converge.

972
00:55:21.318 --> 00:55:23.975
Charlie 27. take the lead.
You're four miles out.

973
00:55:24.113 --> 00:55:26.392
Maintain maximum legal speed.

974
00:55:26.530 --> 00:55:29.291
How soon after you saw the sign
did you make a turn?

975
00:55:29.429 --> 00:55:31.017
-A few minutes.
-Few minutes.

976
00:55:31.155 --> 00:55:33.053
Did you turn right or left?

977
00:55:33.191 --> 00:55:34.676
-Right.
-Right.

978
00:55:34.814 --> 00:55:37.403
Do you remember
the name of the road?

979
00:55:37.541 --> 00:55:38.783
No.

980
00:55:38.921 --> 00:55:40.820
Do you remember anything
about the road?

981
00:55:49.484 --> 00:55:51.209
It was a dirt road.

982
00:55:51.348 --> 00:55:52.763
Dirt road.

983
00:55:52.901 --> 00:55:54.558
Ash Hollow Road.
three and a quarter miles

984
00:55:54.696 --> 00:55:56.905
outside Sykesville. dead end.

985
00:55:57.043 --> 00:55:58.493
Farmhouse at the end.

986
00:55:58.631 --> 00:55:59.908
And found it.

987
00:56:00.046 --> 00:56:01.358
Ash Hollow Road.

988
00:56:01.496 --> 00:56:03.670
Target is a farmhouse.

989
00:56:10.574 --> 00:56:12.817
You've done very well. Jane.

990
00:56:12.955 --> 00:56:15.475
A service to your country.

991
00:56:15.613 --> 00:56:18.892
But I have to ask you
one more thing.

992
00:56:19.030 --> 00:56:23.069
If we can't find Daniel
or we miss him again.

993
00:56:23.207 --> 00:56:25.589
you may need
to stop him yourself

994
00:56:25.727 --> 00:56:27.591
any way you can.

995
00:56:34.218 --> 00:56:36.151
Hang on. BP just tanked.
88 on 62.

996
00:56:36.289 --> 00:56:38.118
Uh. heart rate's dropping...
down to 59.

997
00:56:38.256 --> 00:56:41.121
Uh. O2 is 93 and falling. 91.

998
00:56:45.781 --> 00:56:47.749
92 on 60 and holding.
O2's still dropping. though.

999
00:56:47.887 --> 00:56:48.887
Let's start bagging.

1000
00:56:48.957 --> 00:56:50.268
Make sure you secure the airway.

1001
00:56:50.407 --> 00:56:52.926
High 80s. Keep going.

1002
00:56:53.064 --> 00:56:54.997
Get away!

1003
00:57:00.382 --> 00:57:02.177
Jane.

1004
00:57:03.247 --> 00:57:06.284
What Daniel is trying to do
is wrong.

1005
00:57:06.423 --> 00:57:08.873
It's dangerous.

1006
00:57:09.011 --> 00:57:12.290
It would tip the balance in
an already destabilized world.

1007
00:57:13.291 --> 00:57:14.534
Yes.

1008
00:57:14.672 --> 00:57:16.743
Jane. could you stop him
if you had to?

1009
00:57:16.881 --> 00:57:19.643
No. No.

1010
00:57:22.680 --> 00:57:25.580
"Father. if you be willing.

1011
00:57:25.718 --> 00:57:28.652
"let this cup pass me by.

1012
00:57:28.790 --> 00:57:32.034
Yet not as I will.
but as you will."

1013
00:57:32.172 --> 00:57:34.485
And what did Christ say next?

1014
00:57:36.245 --> 00:57:38.558
"By my will.
thine will be done."

1015
00:57:39.628 --> 00:57:43.114
If the moment comes.
I'll be with you.

1016
00:57:43.252 --> 00:57:45.151
and you'll act. Jane.

1017
00:57:45.289 --> 00:57:48.844
out of love for Daniel.
out of love for the human race.

1018
00:57:52.192 --> 00:57:53.849
Now look around the room.

1019
00:57:55.023 --> 00:57:56.438
Slowly.

1020
00:57:59.959 --> 00:58:01.132
Left to right.

1021
00:58:04.411 --> 00:58:05.827
Stop there.

1022
00:58:07.242 --> 00:58:08.692
