1275
01:22:56.143 --> 01:22:58.143
-Yeah. uh. yeah. I do.
-Uh. you're enjoying this.

1276
01:22:58.214 --> 01:23:00.734
Yeah. I mean. it-it feels good.
It feels good. and then...

1277
01:23:00.872 --> 01:23:02.839
Yeah. but-but... but you know.
You know.

1278
01:23:02.978 --> 01:23:04.576
I mean. you've been driving
like a maniac

1279
01:23:04.600 --> 01:23:06.015
the last few days. you know.

1280
01:23:06.153 --> 01:23:07.913
-How do you know that?
-I just know things.

1281
01:23:08.017 --> 01:23:09.512
It's just. something happened
to me a couple of days ago.

1282
01:23:09.536 --> 01:23:11.434
and now I-I know things.

1283
01:23:11.572 --> 01:23:12.932
Things I don't really
want to know.

1284
01:23:13.022 --> 01:23:14.172
and all the things
I do want to know.

1285
01:23:14.196 --> 01:23:15.542
I don't really know at all.

1286
01:23:15.680 --> 01:23:17.209
so I've just been
kind of rolling with it.

1287
01:23:17.233 --> 01:23:18.831
You know. like...
Oh. wow. you were in jail?

1288
01:23:18.855 --> 01:23:20.375
-That must have been so...
-Hey. hey!

1289
01:23:20.512 --> 01:23:22.100
You see what I mean?

1290
01:23:22.238 --> 01:23:24.378
It's crazy. It's crazy.

1291
01:23:24.516 --> 01:23:28.210
I look at somebody.
and I just drop in on them.

1292
01:23:29.245 --> 01:23:31.937
It's like. for a few seconds.
I am them.

1293
01:23:32.076 --> 01:23:33.698
I see the things
that they've lived.

1294
01:23:33.836 --> 01:23:35.769
It's just like
it's all happening to me. too.

1295
01:23:35.907 --> 01:23:37.357
You know. like-like...

1296
01:23:37.495 --> 01:23:38.990
like right now
your shoulder's killing you.

1297
01:23:39.014 --> 01:23:40.739
Yeah. and you-you just
want to yell.

1298
01:23:40.877 --> 01:23:42.476
-"Keep your eyes on the road!"
-Keep your eyes on the road!

1299
01:23:42.500 --> 01:23:44.167
I know. and you can't stop
thinking about Jane.

1300
01:23:44.191 --> 01:23:45.375
and Jane should be back
at the Monastery St. Clare.

1301
01:23:45.399 --> 01:23:46.918
-You're absolutely right.
-Jane?

1302
01:23:47.056 --> 01:23:49.438
But then yesterday.
I'm driving with Jackson.

1303
01:23:49.576 --> 01:23:51.509
and I flashed on you
without seeing you.

1304
01:23:51.647 --> 01:23:53.062
It was so strong.

1305
01:23:53.200 --> 01:23:54.753
I dropped right in on you

1306
01:23:54.891 --> 01:23:56.559
without even needing
to look at you. and that was

1307
01:23:56.583 --> 01:23:58.319
the first time that crazy shit
has ever happened to me.

1308
01:23:58.343 --> 01:23:59.862
How long you been able
to do this?

1309
01:24:00.000 --> 01:24:01.174
Since yesterday.

1310
01:24:01.312 --> 01:24:02.899
Since the bird.

1311
01:24:03.038 --> 01:24:04.522
-What bird?
-This-this bird.

1312
01:24:04.660 --> 01:24:06.179
Flew in through my window.

1313
01:24:06.317 --> 01:24:08.226
It was beautiful. I looked
at it. and then it-it...

1314
01:24:08.250 --> 01:24:09.250
Was it a cardinal?

1315
01:24:09.354 --> 01:24:10.597
Holy sh... How the...

1316
01:24:10.735 --> 01:24:12.081
You're freaking me the fuck out.

1317
01:24:18.225 --> 01:24:19.606
I was 20. I was in college.

1318
01:24:19.744 --> 01:24:21.504
You were flunking out.
basically. right?

1319
01:24:21.642 --> 01:24:22.954
Yeah. I-I was pretty smart.

1320
01:24:23.092 --> 01:24:24.412
You were. but it was
the partying.

1321
01:24:24.473 --> 01:24:25.553
It was the partying
and the drugs.

1322
01:24:25.577 --> 01:24:27.027
I mean. ketamine? Come on. dude.

1323
01:24:27.165 --> 01:24:28.522
-Could you please stop?
-Sorry. I'm stopping.

1324
01:24:28.546 --> 01:24:29.799
-I was 20. I was in college.
-Yes.

1325
01:24:29.823 --> 01:24:32.412
Uh. it was dark. I-I was in bed.

1326
01:24:32.550 --> 01:24:34.793
and I dreamed that
something was watching me.

1327
01:24:34.931 --> 01:24:36.416
I woke up.
and there was this bird.

1328
01:24:36.554 --> 01:24:37.979
-It was a cardinal.
-In the window.

1329
01:24:38.003 --> 01:24:39.764
and it-it looked at me.
and after that.

1330
01:24:39.902 --> 01:24:41.386
everything just changed.

1331
01:24:41.524 --> 01:24:43.802
I saw things:
context. patterns. art if acting.

1332
01:24:43.940 --> 01:24:45.563
I could see it all.

1333
01:24:45.701 --> 01:24:47.575
Arrays and conditionals
just appeared in my head...

1334
01:24:47.599 --> 01:24:48.980
Fully solved. "If P. then Q."

1335
01:24:49.118 --> 01:24:50.637
Exactly. Solved equations

1336
01:24:50.775 --> 01:24:52.270
-without even thinking...
-And you could read

1337
01:24:52.294 --> 01:24:53.512
eight-bit binary data
like it was English.

1338
01:24:53.536 --> 01:24:54.686
-like it was nothing.
-Yeah.

1339
01:24:54.710 --> 01:24:55.710
How do you know all this?

1340
01:24:55.780 --> 01:24:57.333
I don't. You do.

1341
01:24:57.471 --> 01:24:58.610
God. you hated it.

1342
01:24:58.748 --> 01:25:00.405
-It was a curse.
-Yeah.

1343
01:25:00.543 --> 01:25:02.269
I couldn't relate to anybody.

1344
01:25:02.407 --> 01:25:04.144
I lost every friend I ever had
because I-I couldn't stand

1345
01:25:04.168 --> 01:25:05.652
to be around people.

1346
01:25:05.790 --> 01:25:07.378
Until you met Jane.

1347
01:25:10.967 --> 01:25:12.567
"Don't be afraid
of what you don't know."

1348
01:25:12.659 --> 01:25:14.212
-What?
-That's what you said on TV.

1349
01:25:14.350 --> 01:25:15.800
They said I was
talking nonsense.

1350
01:25:15.938 --> 01:25:17.215
I understood every word.

1351
01:25:17.353 --> 01:25:19.010
What happened to us?

1352
01:25:19.148 --> 01:25:21.012
Oh. my God.

1353
01:25:23.256 --> 01:25:24.498
Who is it?!

1354
01:25:27.191 --> 01:25:28.364
Boyd. stop!

1355
01:25:28.502 --> 01:25:29.607
Boyd!

1356
01:25:38.857 --> 01:25:39.893
Shit.

1357
01:25:40.997 --> 01:25:42.585
We got to jump! We got to bail!

1358
01:25:42.723 --> 01:25:44.518
I can't!
I'm standing on the brakes!

1359
01:25:48.660 --> 01:25:50.490
Oh. my God! Oh. my God!

1360
01:25:52.699 --> 01:25:53.803
No. no. no. no. no. no. no!

1361
01:25:56.254 --> 01:25:57.807
He's backing up! Get out now!

1362
01:26:11.545 --> 01:26:13.271
All right. all right!

1363
01:26:21.831 --> 01:26:23.247
Get to the ladder!

1364
01:26:29.253 --> 01:26:31.186
Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1365
01:26:31.324 --> 01:26:32.635
Okay.

1366
01:27:08.533 --> 01:27:10.535
Go! Jump!

1367
01:27:23.445 --> 01:27:25.136
You got to jump!

1368
01:27:26.102 --> 01:27:27.587
Jump! Now!

1369
01:28:02.242 --> 01:28:03.623
Oh. my God.

1370
01:28:11.803 --> 01:28:14.496
I can't breathe.
I can't breathe.

1371
01:28:15.497 --> 01:28:16.808
I can't breathe.

1372
01:28:18.293 --> 01:28:20.433
-It's okay. It's okay.
-I can't breathe.

1373
01:28:20.571 --> 01:28:22.203
- I think you're having
a panic attack. - Oh. my God.

1374
01:28:22.227 --> 01:28:24.333
-It's okay. It's okay.
-Oh. my God. Oh. my God.

1375
01:28:24.471 --> 01:28:26.162
-It's okay. I'm used to 'em.
-My hands.

1376
01:28:26.301 --> 01:28:28.026
-We're okay.
-It's like my dad.

1377
01:28:28.164 --> 01:28:29.694
-It's like my dad. My hands.
-No. no. no. No. no. no. no.

1378
01:28:29.718 --> 01:28:31.547
It's like Parkinson's.
It's like Parkinson's.

1379
01:28:31.685 --> 01:28:33.042
It's not the same thing.
It's not that.

1380
01:28:33.066 --> 01:28:34.585
Yes. it is. It's the same.

1381
01:28:34.723 --> 01:28:36.563
No. he couldn't control it.
I can't control it.

1382
01:28:36.621 --> 01:28:38.105
-I can't control it.
-You can.

1383
01:28:38.243 --> 01:28:40.867
Oh. my God. I ran away from him.

1384
01:28:41.005 --> 01:28:43.697
- I didn't want to be
around him anymore. - No. no. no. Stop.

1385
01:28:43.835 --> 01:28:45.561
-I want this gone!
-Okay.

1386
01:28:45.699 --> 01:28:48.461
I just want it gone!
I want it gone!

1387
01:28:48.599 --> 01:28:51.187
I want it gone! I just have
no mind of my own anymore!

1388
01:28:51.326 --> 01:28:53.120
Okay. stop! Stop!
Stop talking! Stop.

1389
01:28:53.258 --> 01:28:54.398
Give me your hands.

1390
01:28:54.536 --> 01:28:55.816
-Okay. look at me.
-No. no. no.

1391
01:28:55.882 --> 01:28:57.308
-Look at me.
-I-I'm gonna see things.

1392
01:28:57.332 --> 01:28:58.919
-I'm gonna see things. Please.
-Okay.

1393
01:28:59.057 --> 01:29:01.137
Breathe through your nose.
Breathe through your nose.

1394
01:29:01.543 --> 01:29:03.130
That's it. Okay.

1395
01:29:03.268 --> 01:29:05.201
I can't feel my hands.

1396
01:29:05.340 --> 01:29:07.169
Okay. Okay.

1397
01:29:07.307 --> 01:29:08.998
Okay. give me your hands.
Come on.

1398
01:29:09.136 --> 01:29:10.724
Come on. Put your hands there.

1399
01:29:10.862 --> 01:29:12.726
Feel that. Okay. you feel that?

1400
01:29:12.864 --> 01:29:14.418
I'm here. I'm here.

1401
01:29:14.556 --> 01:29:16.005
We're here.

1402
01:29:16.143 --> 01:29:17.628
-We're okay.
-Okay.

1403
01:29:18.836 --> 01:29:20.216
-We're okay.
-We're okay.

1404
01:29:20.355 --> 01:29:22.460
We're okay.

1405
01:29:22.598 --> 01:29:25.290
We're okay now. You're okay.

1406
01:29:29.674 --> 01:29:31.676
We're okay.

1407
01:29:31.814 --> 01:29:33.091
Okay.

1408
01:29:37.855 --> 01:29:39.581
Thank you.

1409
01:29:42.722 --> 01:29:45.042
Kellner called in from a gas
station outside Mount Leonard.

1410
01:29:45.138 --> 01:29:46.418
I'll meet Santiago and his crew.

1411
01:29:46.519 --> 01:29:48.417
We can be there
in a couple hours.

1412
01:29:51.178 --> 01:29:53.284
H-Hugo?

1413
01:29:53.422 --> 01:29:54.862
Could everyone leave
the staging area

1414
01:29:54.941 --> 01:29:56.321
for a minute. please?

1415
01:29:56.460 --> 01:29:59.221
-Now. please! Out!
-Yeah. Okay. let's go.

1416
01:30:05.572 --> 01:30:07.194
Hello. Hugo.

1417
01:30:12.855 --> 01:30:14.961
Noah. please.

1418
01:30:16.031 --> 01:30:18.043
It's terribly misguided for you
to dive with that thing.

1419
01:30:18.067 --> 01:30:19.931
It's not a magic wand.

1420
01:30:20.069 --> 01:30:21.795
And it's not a weapon.
but it has functions

1421
01:30:21.933 --> 01:30:24.798
very far beyond
your limited use of it.

1422
01:30:24.936 --> 01:30:29.424
Kellner was an experiencer.
wasn't he?

1423
01:30:29.562 --> 01:30:31.426
That's why
I couldn't dive on him.

1424
01:30:31.564 --> 01:30:33.738
Yes.

1425
01:30:33.876 --> 01:30:35.637
He was.

1426
01:30:37.501 --> 01:30:41.505
And In Vivo 17
told you to recruit him?

1427
01:30:42.816 --> 01:30:44.646
Not in any way you'd understand.

1428
01:30:44.784 --> 01:30:46.371
If this is all their plan. Hugo.

1429
01:30:46.510 --> 01:30:48.960
you can be sure it's
in their interests. not ours.

1430
01:30:49.098 --> 01:30:51.446
That's a very lonely way
to look at the world.

1431
01:30:51.584 --> 01:30:52.964
No. don't condescend to me.

1432
01:30:53.102 --> 01:30:54.518
I'm listening to you. Noah.

1433
01:30:54.656 --> 01:30:56.623
Something I've learned
quite a bit about.

1434
01:30:56.761 --> 01:30:58.176
From your friends?

1435
01:30:58.314 --> 01:30:59.937
Yes.

1436
01:31:00.075 --> 01:31:02.871
They regard empathy
as an evolutionary advantage.

1437
01:31:03.009 --> 01:31:05.494
as the foremost
evolutionary advantage.

1438
01:31:05.632 --> 01:31:09.602
in fact. the core
of animate existence.

1439
01:31:09.740 --> 01:31:11.811
Our rejection
of this understanding

1440
01:31:11.949 --> 01:31:14.123
is leading us to our extinction.

1441
01:31:15.159 --> 01:31:18.162
And is your bleeding heart
why you helped it escape?

1442
01:31:20.129 --> 01:31:21.683
Five years ago.

1443
01:31:21.821 --> 01:31:23.685
That was you. wasn't it?

1444
01:31:25.445 --> 01:31:26.688
Yes.

1445
01:31:27.999 --> 01:31:30.830
The utter insanity
of that act aside.

1446
01:31:30.968 --> 01:31:33.177
how could you lie to me
for five years

1447
01:31:33.315 --> 01:31:34.903
every time you walked
through the door?

1448
01:31:35.041 --> 01:31:37.699
Everything you said to me.
it was all diversion.

1449
01:31:39.701 --> 01:31:42.876
When precisely did you lose
your bearings?

1450
01:31:43.014 --> 01:31:45.361
Around the time you lost yours.

1451
01:31:47.812 --> 01:31:49.400
When you lost her.

1452
01:31:53.784 --> 01:31:56.372
You lost her and almost
immediately were lost to me.

1453
01:31:56.511 --> 01:31:57.753
Because you shut down.

1454
01:31:57.891 --> 01:31:59.341
Do not presume to know me.

1455
01:31:59.479 --> 01:32:00.836
When she died.
you reduced everyone

1456
01:32:00.860 --> 01:32:02.378
to need-to-know. including me.

1457
01:32:02.517 --> 01:32:03.690
Because you were very clear.

1458
01:32:03.828 --> 01:32:05.209
All you needed to know was them.

1459
01:32:05.347 --> 01:32:07.522
and they are not knowable.
not by us.

1460
01:32:07.660 --> 01:32:10.179
They will be.

1461
01:32:10.317 --> 01:32:12.423
In Vivo 17 is nonhuman

1462
01:32:12.561 --> 01:32:14.218
but nearer to God. Noah.
than you or I.

1463
01:32:14.356 --> 01:32:16.323
You don't need to fear them.

1464
01:32:17.324 --> 01:32:19.257
I fear us.

1465
01:32:19.395 --> 01:32:22.433
The entire reason WARDEX exists
is because of our knowledge.

1466
01:32:22.571 --> 01:32:26.644
certain that the human race
cannot accept what we know.

1467
01:32:26.782 --> 01:32:28.462
That truth will upend
all established order

1468
01:32:28.577 --> 01:32:29.889
across the entire world.

1469
01:32:30.027 --> 01:32:32.443
The archive Kellner stole
is a virus

1470
01:32:32.581 --> 01:32:36.758
against which
the world has zero immunity.

1471
01:32:36.896 --> 01:32:39.243
I have spent 35 years
protecting...

1472
01:32:39.381 --> 01:32:40.624
Your own wealth and power...

1473
01:32:40.762 --> 01:32:42.418
that's all
you've been protecting.

1474
01:32:42.557 --> 01:32:45.352
Noah. Noah.

1475
01:32:45.490 --> 01:32:47.596
There is an essential need
in all of us to believe

1476
01:32:47.734 --> 01:32:50.979
and an equal need
to be believed.

1477
01:32:51.117 --> 01:32:53.222
You've violated
every standard of evidence.

1478
01:32:53.360 --> 01:32:54.983
You've infantilized anyone

1479
01:32:55.121 --> 01:32:57.675
who only wanted to understand
what they've witnessed.

1480
01:32:57.813 --> 01:33:00.609
You've brutally stifled
their questions.

1481
01:33:00.747 --> 01:33:03.336
shouted them down.
ridiculed and shamed

1482
01:33:03.474 --> 01:33:05.165
and overridden them
for the crime

1483
01:33:05.303 --> 01:33:07.271
of simply being astonished.

1484
01:33:07.409 --> 01:33:10.101
We believe the believers
and then deny the world

1485
01:33:10.239 --> 01:33:12.000
the chance to believe them. too.

1486
01:33:12.138 --> 01:33:14.658
But people keep wondering.
encountering the unknown.

1487
01:33:14.796 --> 01:33:16.418
telling others
of their experiences.

1488
01:33:16.556 --> 01:33:18.834
They are starved for the truth.

1489
01:33:18.972 --> 01:33:22.458
This 79-year terror campaign

1490
01:33:22.597 --> 01:33:26.083
of obfuscation. lies
and cover-up has to end!

1491
01:33:26.221 --> 01:33:28.016
We're ready to show you
a demonstration.

1492
01:33:28.154 --> 01:33:30.501
-Get out! Get out!
-Sorry. sir. we have...

1493
01:33:30.639 --> 01:33:32.641
Turn around and get out now!

1494
01:33:38.129 --> 01:33:40.994
Pull up the 12 who didn't
show up to work yesterday.

1495
01:33:41.132 --> 01:33:44.032
I need faces
who are with him right now.

1496
01:33:44.170 --> 01:33:46.655
-Her.
-Grace Zhao. neuro-services.

1497
01:33:46.793 --> 01:33:48.312
-Him.
-Nathan Twinning.

1498
01:33:48.450 --> 01:33:49.865
Hugo's chief aide.

1499
01:33:50.003 --> 01:33:51.567
Got a back door
into their mobile providers.

1500
01:33:51.591 --> 01:33:53.282
Hang on.

1501
01:33:56.354 --> 01:34:00.773
They shut down their phones
last night... right here.

1502
01:34:02.153 --> 01:34:03.914
I'll project their routes ahead
to overlap.

1503
01:34:04.052 --> 01:34:06.710
I can give you the AI model
within a quarter-mile radius.

1504
01:34:15.408 --> 01:34:17.859
Sister Maura. Sister.

1505
01:34:26.143 --> 01:34:27.558
Jane?

1506
01:34:27.696 --> 01:34:29.146
Where are you. Jane?

1507
01:34:32.011 --> 01:34:33.564
Does God love us?

1508
01:34:33.702 --> 01:34:36.601
I don't mean. does he love us?
I know he does.

1509
01:34:36.740 --> 01:34:40.467
Does he love only us?

1510
01:34:40.605 --> 01:34:42.780
'Cause Genesis says that
we're his supreme creation.

1511
01:34:42.918 --> 01:34:45.576
but do you think
it's possible that...

1512
01:34:45.714 --> 01:34:47.164
On Earth.

1513
01:34:48.475 --> 01:34:49.614
What?

1514
01:34:49.753 --> 01:34:51.271
Genesis.

1515
01:34:51.409 --> 01:34:56.035
It says we are God's
supreme creation on Earth.

1516
01:35:05.182 --> 01:35:07.184
Do you think
there could be others?

1517
01:35:08.875 --> 01:35:10.912
Yes.

1518
01:35:11.050 --> 01:35:12.637
I would think so.

1519
01:35:12.776 --> 01:35:16.331
Why would he make
such a vast universe.

1520
01:35:16.469 --> 01:35:20.507
yet save it only for us?

1521
01:35:21.612 --> 01:35:26.721
If you found out
we weren't alone. if...

